        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 8:22PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 822 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Killen, or 13 miles northeast of Florence, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Florence, Athens, Muscle Shoals, Rogersville, Killen, Lexington, St.
Florian, Underwood-Petersville, Anderson, and Lester.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
